<head>LION</head>
    <list type="translations">
        <item xml:lang="zh">獅子</item>
    </list>
<div type="definition">
<p>MOST STRONG AND MOST BIG FELINE.</p>
    </div>
<div type="notes">
<div type="old-chinese-criteria">
<p>1. The standard word for a lion is shī 獅, usually written 師, or 獅子／師子.</p>
        </div>
<div type="modern-chinese-criteria">
<p>獅</p>
<p>獅子</p>
<p>獸王</p>
<p>狻猊 refers to a legendary lion-like beast of prey.</p>
<p>rough draft to BEGIN TO identify synonym group members for analysis, based on CL etc. 18.11.2003. CH ／</p>
        </div>
